issues.description: The profile Profile1 Fibre Channel connection 1 has a configured speed of 1 Gb which will be translated to auto in OneView.
issues.recommendation: If a configured speed of auto is not appropriate, do not proceed with the migration.

issues.description: The profile Profile1 Fibre Channel connection 3 has a configured speed of 1 Gb which will be translated to auto in OneView.
issues.recommendation: If a configured speed of auto is not appropriate, do not proceed with the migration.

issues.description: Profile Profile2 has one or more connections configured with Use-BIOS boot settings. OneView does not support profile connections configured with a mixture of Use-BIOS and other boot settings.
issues.recommendation: The Virtual Connect Use-BIOS boot setting will be automatically changed to not bootable in OneView.

issues.description: Profile Profile2 Fibre Channel connection 3 is not mapped to a server port. This connection will not be transferred because the migration of unmapped Fibre Channel connections is not supported in this release.
issues.recommendation: Without user action, the connection will not be transferred to OneView.  Additional Fibre Channel ports may also be added to the server.

issues.description: Profile Profile4 FCoE connection 1 is configured for factory MAC and a factory WWN of 10:00:1C:C1:DE:EE:A1:89. The WWN for this connection may change after migration to OneView.
issues.recommendation: After the migration task has completed, validate the WWNs of the migrated profiles for any potential changes. If a WWN change occurred, change the SAN fabric and storage configuration to reflect the new WWNs before powering on the servers.
